\keepn \f15 \cf13 \fs36 \b \pard \keepn \f15 Getting Started\par \b0 \pard \f15 \fs28 \pard \f15 \fs36 \b \cf0 What is UnfragWorks Server?\fs28 \b0 \par UnfragWorks Server is a utility to remove the redundant space from SolidWorks files.  UnfragWorks Server can reduce the size of SolidWorks files by up to 50% with absolutely no loss of data or information.  UnfragWorks Server will constantly save you hard disk space by continually removing redundant space from SolidWorks files.\par \par When first started, UnfragWorks Server will scan all the specified directories and subdirectories for SolidWorks files.  These are added to an initial list of files for unfragging.  During it's first unfragging run, UnfragWorks Server will attempt to unfrag all of these files.  These are then marked as unfragged and no further attempts will be made to unfrag them unless they change.\par \par UnfragWorks Server then keeps watches over user specified directories and subdirectories for changes in SolidWorks files.  When UnfragWorks Server detects a changed file, it notes this and will unfragment all changed files at a user specified time.\par \par \par see also:\tab \b \uldb Unfragmenting\b0 \uldb0 \v Unfragmenting\v0 \par \par \par UnfragWorks Server installs as an NT service and runs transparently in the background.  An icon with a right mouse button menu (figure below) is installed in the system tray.\par \par \pard \fs0 \{bml ICON.BMP\}\fs28 \par \pard \par \par \pard \fs0 \{bml RMB.SHG\}\fs28 \par \pard \par Move cursor over figure to go to links.\par \par \par \fs36 \b When does UnfragWorks Server run?\fs28 \b0 \par UnfragWorks Server runs at the time, frequency and priority which you specify.  The configuration settings may be accessed by right clicking on the UnfragWorks Server icon in the system tray and selecting the 'Configure' menu.  This will bring up the configuration dialog page.  Note that this will temporarily stop UnfragWorks Server.  When the configuration dialog is closed, UnfragWorks Server will be restarted.\par \par \par see also:\tab \b \uldb Scheduling\b0 \uldb0 \v Scheduling\v0 \par \par \page 
